comments.body:
Oh I see the issue lsr vs asr.
Anyways I found things GCC does not handle because it does not convert ashr to lshr.
And a testcase which LLVM does not handle either due to the ashr vs lshr that is similar to this one:
```
int f(int a, unsigned b, int c)
{
  b &= 0xffff;
  return (c >> a) ^ (b >> a);
}
```
